\c 3\ s The people who helped to build the wall in Jerusalem
\p
\v 1 Then we began rebuilding the fortress of the city of Jerusalem and its gates. Here is a list of people working, each in his group.
\p Sheep Gate and the surrounding wall to Mea Tower and Hananeel Tower:
\li2 High Priest Eliashib and other priests. They were the ones who installed the doors and built the walls and then inaugurated it.
\li2
\v 2 Groups of people from the city of Jericho.
\li2 The group of Zakur son of Imri. Both of them built the wall.
\p
\v 3 The Fish Gate and  the surrounding walls:
\li2 The Hassenaah family installed the beams, the doors and made locks and bars.
\li2
\v 4
\li2 Meremot's group, son of Uriah, grandson of Hakos.
\li2 Meshullam group, son of Berechiah, grandson of Meshezabel.
\li2 The Zadok group, the son of Baana.
\li2
\v 5 The people from Tekoa (they joined in the work even though the leader of their city refused to help). Hey were the fourth groups that repaired the wall.
\p
\v 6 The Old Gate and its surrounding walls:
\li2 The group of Joiada, the son of Paseah and Meshullam, the son of Besodeiah, set the beams and the gates, complete with locks and bars.
\li2
\v 7 Melatiah the Gibeonite, Jadon of Meronoth, also the people of the cities of Gibeon and Mizpah which were in the territory of the governor of the region west of the Euphrates River.
\li2 8 Uzziel son of Harhaiah, who was skilled at working with gold, and
\li2 Hananiah,one of the  perfume-maker. They built the walls of Jerusalem up to the Broad Wall.
\li2
\v 9 The Repaya Son of Hur, the official [@ authorities // in charge] over half of the Jerusalem area, repairs the next wall.
\li2
\v 10 Jedaiah, the son of Harumaph repaired the city wall opposite his house.
\li2 The group of Hattush  son of Hasabneya.
\li2
\v 11 The group of Malchijah the son of Harim and Hasshub the son of Pahath-Moab built the next section as well and  the Tower of furnaces.
\li2
\v 12 Shallum the son of Hallohesh, who was the leader of the other half of Jerusalem, with his daughters.
\p
\v 13 The Valley Gate and its surrounding walls:
\li2 Hanun and the inhabiants of Zanoah set the doors, made locks and latches for the gate, and repaired the wall for 450 meters, up to the Dung Gate.
\p
\v 14 Garbage Disposal Gate:
\li2 The Malchijan group of the sons of Rechab, ruler of the Beth-haccherem division, repaired the door and made locks and bars.
\p
\v 15 The Fountain Gate and its surrounding walls:
\li2 Shallun the son of Colhozeh, the ruler of the distric of Mizpah, repaired the door and locks and bars. He also built Shelah by the royal garden, as far the stairs that go down from the City of David.
\li2
\v 16 The group of Nehemiah the son of Azbuk, the official [@ authority // in charge] over half of Beth-Zur's territory, rebuilt the wall to the place opposite David's burial place, the artificial pond, and the home of the heroes.
\li2
\v 17 Rehum son of Bani with the group of the Levites.
\li2 Hashabiah, leader of half division of  Keilah, with his group from his region.
\li2
\v 18 Bavvai the son of Henadad, leader of another half of the Kehila region, along with people from his area.